## Installer image - with "default"
##   It should contain everything offered in tasksel during initial installation so all kali-linux-* except:
##   - kali-linux-everything
##   - kali-linux-large
##   NOTE: We would like to provide kali-linux-large in our "default" installer images
##         but we end up with ISO images that are too big for our CDN.
##         So disable it for now.
##
## $ ./build.sh --variant default

## Installer images always want these
kali-linux-firmware

## Graphical desktop
##   For the complete list see: https://www.kali.org/docs/general-use/metapackages/
kali-desktop-xfce
kali-desktop-gnome
kali-desktop-kde

## Metapackages
##   You can customize the set of Kali metapackages (groups of tools) available in the installer ISO
##   For the complete list see: https://www.kali.org/tools/kali-meta/
kali-linux-core
kali-tools-top10
kali-linux-default
#kali-linux-large

## Extra Kali packages/tools/applications
##   For the complete list see: https://www.kali.org/tools/
##                              https://pkg.kali.org/
#<package>
